1
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:21,956
All eyes will be on you.

2
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:23,249
You should be prepared.

3
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:26,127
Yes, I was expecting this.

4
00:01:26,795 --> 00:01:28,129
But how should I handle this?

5
00:01:28,213 --> 00:01:29,631
Just hang in there.

6
00:01:30,131 --> 00:01:31,549
It won't last long.

7
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:37,472
I won't have to go to court, right?

8
00:01:39,599 --> 00:01:40,600
I'll make sure you don't.

9
00:01:40,683 --> 00:01:42,435
I'll be counting on the two of you.

10
00:02:08,586 --> 00:02:11,714
JEONGHAN DAILY

11
00:02:20,056 --> 00:02:21,975
Let's not go.

12
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:24,227
-Why not?
-I think he's caught on.

13
00:02:26,771 --> 00:02:30,233
Call the rest of the team
and tell them to come to the office

14
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:32,402
instead of going home.

15
00:02:34,112 --> 00:02:37,407
I'll be there around 11:00 p.m.

16
00:02:37,991 --> 00:02:40,160
Yes. Okay, bye.

17
00:02:43,496 --> 00:02:46,624
I heard her dad is a death-row convict
who killed two people.

18
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:48,918
So what? It's not like she killed them.

19
00:02:49,002 --> 00:02:51,254
Still, she gives me the creeps.

20
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:53,965
What would she have learned
from a father like that?

21
00:02:54,549 --> 00:02:55,884
And I don't like her eyes.

22
00:02:55,967 --> 00:02:59,470
You're just prejudiced against her.
She grew up in a difficult environment.

23
00:02:59,554 --> 00:03:02,515
Do you owe her something?

24
00:03:02,599 --> 00:03:04,976
What? Why would I owe her anything?

25
00:03:05,059 --> 00:03:08,271
Then why are you being so nice to her?
You're never like this.

26
00:03:08,354 --> 00:03:10,815
Because I'm running low on testosterone.

27
00:03:10,899 --> 00:03:12,901
Because of you, I'm losing all my hair,

28
00:03:12,984 --> 00:03:16,195
my testosterone levels have gone down,
and I always find myself crying.

29
00:03:16,279 --> 00:03:18,948
It's all your fault, you darn brat.

30
00:03:20,909 --> 00:03:23,369
My gosh, what's wrong with him?

31
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:37,467
Come in.

32
00:03:43,848 --> 00:03:46,517
Do you like your room?

33
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:50,480
Here.

34
00:03:51,439 --> 00:03:52,440
I just peeled them.

35
00:04:03,534 --> 00:04:06,955
This bed is quite old.

36
00:04:08,289 --> 00:04:10,458
But it'll be better than the ones
in the hospital.

37
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:15,505
The mattress is still okay.

38
00:04:15,588 --> 00:04:16,798
You can save my dad, right?

39
00:04:18,925 --> 00:04:20,551
He didn't kill anyone.

40
00:04:20,635 --> 00:04:22,553
You know that.

41
00:04:22,637 --> 00:04:24,347
I'll try my best

42
00:04:25,765 --> 00:04:27,141
and do everything I can.

43
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:28,893
What if my dad

44
00:04:32,021 --> 00:04:33,940
ends up getting executed?

45
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,736
Who can I blame when that happens?

46
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:43,074
My dad told me

47
00:04:44,075 --> 00:04:46,703
to forget about him
as if he never existed in my life.

48
00:04:47,787 --> 00:04:49,163
But how can I do that?

49
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:52,625
He gave birth to me and raised me.

50
00:04:54,127 --> 00:04:55,253
He's still my dad.

51
00:04:56,796 --> 00:04:58,256
Your dad is still alive.

52
00:05:00,383 --> 00:05:01,592
I was the one

53
00:05:02,719 --> 00:05:04,262
who arrested him.

54
00:05:06,139 --> 00:05:07,849
And I'm the one

55
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:11,436
who can undo that.

56
00:05:26,034 --> 00:05:28,369
You have something to tell me
about Lee Dae-cheol?

57
00:05:30,496 --> 00:05:34,083
Lee Dae-cheol was sentenced to death
for having murdered

58
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:37,003
a female college student
and a police detective.

59
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:41,257
The student's name was Yoon Ji-seon.
She was an art student.

60
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:45,136
It turns out she drew a portrait
for someone before she died.

61
00:05:45,219 --> 00:05:50,725
And I have circumstantial evidence
that the person might've killed her.

62
00:05:50,808 --> 00:05:52,143
Who's that?

63
00:05:52,226 --> 00:05:54,103
The president
of Incheon Jeil Investment Trust.

64
00:05:54,604 --> 00:05:55,897
Oh Jong-tae.

65
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:02,820
-Do you have evidence?
-Oh Jong-tae's alibi was fabricated.

66
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:05,323
-And?
-And there's evidence

67
00:06:05,406 --> 00:06:08,242
that Lee Dae-cheol was somewhere else
when the victim was murdered.

68
00:06:08,826 --> 00:06:11,079
They're both indirect evidence.
They won't be admitted.

69
00:06:11,162 --> 00:06:14,332
Both the case and trial were carried out
based on the wrong evidence.

70
00:06:14,415 --> 00:06:16,793
I think it's more than enough
to ask for a retrial.

71
00:06:17,835 --> 00:06:20,129
A retrial? Do you think that will be easy?

72
00:06:20,713 --> 00:06:21,714
No, it will be hard.

73
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:24,801
More so if Oh Jong-tae
turns out to be the real culprit.

74
00:06:26,928 --> 00:06:29,097
He's one of the wealthiest men in Incheon.

75
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:31,849
He'll use all his connections
in the legal and political circles,

76
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,726
and the police force to stop the retrial.

77
00:06:33,810 --> 00:06:34,852
And even

78
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:38,064
the press.

79
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,067
Someone once told me

80
00:06:41,150 --> 00:06:44,445
that the best way to cover up a case

81
00:06:44,529 --> 00:06:47,698
is to get rid of the victim forever.

82
00:06:48,658 --> 00:06:51,828
Lee Dae-cheol almost got murdered in jail.

83
00:06:51,911 --> 00:06:54,539
But that plan failed,
and not too long after that,

84
00:06:54,622 --> 00:06:57,500
the government gave an execution order
for the first time in 20 years.

85
00:06:57,583 --> 00:07:01,796
What if the purpose of that execution
is to get rid of Lee Dae-cheol?

86
00:07:01,879 --> 00:07:05,341
And what if the actual culprit
is behind all this?

87
00:07:06,134 --> 00:07:08,469
It'd be impossible for an ordinary person.

88
00:07:09,262 --> 00:07:12,515
But it's possible if it's Oh Jong-tae.

89
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:19,480
I also know Oh Jong-tae.

90
00:07:20,273 --> 00:07:21,691
He's a very powerful man.

91
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:25,278
He also helped my brother get elected.

92
00:07:27,196 --> 00:07:29,782
But he's just someone
who has a little power in the suburbs.

93
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:34,954
An execution order is an important issue
that requires the President's approval.

94
00:07:35,037 --> 00:07:38,958
Do you think he's powerful enough
to have influence over the President?

95
00:07:40,460 --> 00:07:43,754
If your speculation is right,
Oh Jong-tae wouldn't be the culprit.

96
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:48,426
It's someone
who's more powerful than he is.

97
00:07:58,436 --> 00:07:59,604
Hey, Detective Oh.

98
00:08:01,772 --> 00:08:02,773
Right now?

99
00:08:06,235 --> 00:08:07,361
Okay.

100
00:08:11,282 --> 00:08:12,116
Yoo Jeong-seok,

101
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:14,410
the head of the Current Affairs Team
at Jeonghan Daily.

102
00:08:14,494 --> 00:08:16,412
And his older brother is

103
00:08:17,413 --> 00:08:19,290
Assemblyman Yoo Jeong-ryeol.

104
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:22,168
He might become
the next Minister of Justice.

105
00:08:29,467 --> 00:08:33,137
I won't have to go to court, right?

106
00:08:33,221 --> 00:08:34,972
I'll be counting on the two of you.

107
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:42,188
The head of the Current Affairs Team
at Jeonghan Daily

108
00:08:42,271 --> 00:08:44,607
and the next Minister of Justice
are both watching his back?

109
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:46,275
My goodness.

110
00:08:47,068 --> 00:08:50,154
-This is giving me a headache.
-He met him on purpose to prove a point.

111
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:54,492
He wanted to show us that he's friends
with someone very powerful.

112
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:59,080
Do-chang.

113
00:08:59,163 --> 00:09:02,750
Why are you still keeping
the guys at work?

114
00:09:05,628 --> 00:09:08,631
Do-chang, this is wrong.

115
00:09:08,714 --> 00:09:11,384
Let's be honest.
You're doing this for personal reasons.

116
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:13,219
-Am I wrong?
-What?

117
00:09:13,302 --> 00:09:15,680
-What's wrong with you?
-Move.

118
00:09:15,763 --> 00:09:17,098
You know I'm right.

119
00:09:17,848 --> 00:09:18,849
Do-chang.

120
00:09:21,185 --> 00:09:25,147
Just focus on catching Joo Dong-pal.
That's our job.

121
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:29,902
Why do you have to keep the boys here
for something personal?

122
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:30,903
Jae-hong.

123
00:09:31,445 --> 00:09:32,697
We want to do this.

124
00:09:32,780 --> 00:09:36,075
Oh, come on. Stop being funny.

125
00:09:36,158 --> 00:09:38,119
You all need to wake up.

126
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:40,997
Your career will get messed up
regardless of how this case turns out.

127
00:09:41,497 --> 00:09:42,373
Do-chang, look at me.

128
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:44,166
Let me ask you a favor.

129
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:49,088
If you still have
at least a little bit of conscience left,

130
00:09:49,171 --> 00:09:50,756
let the boys go home

131
00:09:51,299 --> 00:09:53,801
instead of ruining their lives!

132
00:09:53,884 --> 00:09:56,929
Jae-hong, what's wrong with you?

133
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:59,140
Did you say we represent the police?

134
00:10:00,474 --> 00:10:04,729
Just be honest
and say you need suicide bombers.

135
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:06,772
-Darn it!
-Jae-hong.

136
00:10:09,108 --> 00:10:10,651
My gosh.

137
00:10:10,735 --> 00:10:11,902
What's with him?

138
00:10:14,739 --> 00:10:18,534
Jae-hong is right.
You guys can decide what to do.

139
00:10:20,328 --> 00:10:21,579
-Ji-hyeok.
-Yes?

140
00:10:21,662 --> 00:10:25,207
Can I see that evidence you told me about
regarding the fabricated video footage?

141
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:26,751
Okay.

142
00:10:26,834 --> 00:10:28,336
The rest of you can leave.

143
00:10:29,378 --> 00:10:30,630
Thanks for your help.

144
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:32,715
Why is everything so complicated?

145
00:10:32,798 --> 00:10:34,175
It's simple.

146
00:10:34,258 --> 00:10:37,345
It means we're going to get fired
if we keep helping Do-chang.

147
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:41,807
How will they fire us?
We're public officials.

148
00:10:41,891 --> 00:10:46,312
They might not fire us,
but they'll send us to the countryside.

149
00:10:46,395 --> 00:10:48,689
We'll still get paid.

150
00:10:48,773 --> 00:10:51,067
But we won't be able to have
a successful career.

151
00:10:51,609 --> 00:10:54,862
If I cared about that, I wouldn't have
applied for the violent crimes unit.

152
00:10:54,945 --> 00:10:57,448
-You have a point.
-Isn't that Jae-hong?

153
00:10:57,531 --> 00:10:58,741
Where?

154
00:11:00,534 --> 00:11:04,205
Is that fool going to drive
after drinking that much?

155
00:11:04,288 --> 00:11:09,293
How many times do I need to tell you
that Do-chang is after Joo Dong-pal?

156
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:10,544
Think about it.

157
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:13,464
What would he gain
from digging up Lee Dae-cheol's case?

158
00:11:14,048 --> 00:11:16,175
My gosh. Hey.

159
00:11:16,717 --> 00:11:19,095
Do you think I'm your minion?

160
00:11:19,178 --> 00:11:21,847
Forget it. Just do whatever you want.
Do whatever you want!

161
00:11:27,144 --> 00:11:29,063
Darn this.

162
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,609
This is so humiliating.

163
00:11:34,568 --> 00:11:37,738
How did I end up in such a big mess?

164
00:11:38,322 --> 00:11:41,242
Gosh, I'm still paying for this.

165
00:11:41,325 --> 00:11:42,326
This is driving me crazy.

166
00:11:43,411 --> 00:11:46,288
LIEUTENANT YOON SANG-MI

167
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:53,129
You're getting a call from Yoon Sang-mi.

168
00:11:54,213 --> 00:11:56,340
Yoon Sang-mi
from the Civil Petition Division.

169
00:11:56,424 --> 00:11:58,926
Gosh, I can't believe this.

170
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:13,232
We should apply for a retrial

171
00:12:13,315 --> 00:12:14,608
before it's too late.

172
00:12:14,692 --> 00:12:17,027
We should, considering the situation.

173
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:19,405
But we don't have enough time.

174
00:12:19,488 --> 00:12:22,783
It's hard to win a retrial
even if you prepare it for years.

175
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:26,036
We'll just have to do what we can.
There's no other way.

176
00:12:26,120 --> 00:12:27,997
Detective Kwon said earlier

177
00:12:28,080 --> 00:12:31,417
that your career will get messed up
regardless of how this case turns out.

178
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:32,626
He's right, you know.

179
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:34,545
Are you guys okay with that?

180
00:12:35,379 --> 00:12:37,465
The worst thing that can happen to me
is getting fired.

181
00:12:37,548 --> 00:12:40,968
But if things go wrong,
Lee Dae-cheol will die.

182
00:12:41,719 --> 00:12:43,721
What do you think I should do?

183
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:53,522
Be honest with us.

184
00:12:54,398 --> 00:12:56,192
Yoon Sang-mi has you by the balls, right?

185
00:13:01,572 --> 00:13:02,990
Jae-hong, by any chance…

186
00:13:03,073 --> 00:13:05,201
What? By any chance what?

187
00:13:05,284 --> 00:13:08,412
Dong-uk, what in the world
are you thinking?

188
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:11,165
You all heard what he said over the phone.

189
00:13:11,248 --> 00:13:13,167
Why do you think he mentioned Do-chang?

190
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:15,419
She must've asked him to keep an eye on…

191
00:13:15,503 --> 00:13:18,464
Hey, you punk.
What do you know about Jae-hong?

192
00:13:18,547 --> 00:13:22,801
Do you have any idea
how much he actually respects Do-chang?

193
00:13:23,677 --> 00:13:25,888
What if Dong-uk is right?

194
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:31,143
What if he's right, you punks?

195
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:32,645
What's wrong with you?

196
00:13:32,728 --> 00:13:34,730
What are you saying?

197
00:13:35,898 --> 00:13:38,692
Think about it, guys.

198
00:13:40,194 --> 00:13:42,196
Who do you think will last longer
in this team?

199
00:13:43,614 --> 00:13:46,033
Me or Do-chang?

200
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,661
Damn it.

201
00:14:00,714 --> 00:14:01,715
Thank you.

202
00:14:03,467 --> 00:14:06,095
-Did you report this to your superiors?
-This case?

203
00:14:07,054 --> 00:14:08,639
Yes, I did.

204
00:14:08,722 --> 00:14:12,226
Did you also tell Mr. Yoo
who met up with Oh Jong-tae earlier?

205
00:14:12,309 --> 00:14:15,646
Of course. He's my direct supervisor.

206
00:14:15,729 --> 00:14:17,273
They looked pretty close.

207
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:20,150
He won't be glad to hear
that we're after Oh Jong-tae.

208
00:14:21,443 --> 00:14:24,905
It won't be good for you
to get on his bad side.

209
00:14:26,907 --> 00:14:30,119
Right. You have a point.

210
00:14:34,665 --> 00:14:37,251
Why go against him
when I just got a job at the head office?

211
00:14:37,334 --> 00:14:41,338
Plus, this case will have to butt heads
with the cops, prosecution, and judiciary.

212
00:14:41,922 --> 00:14:45,467
If I do anything to cross them,
they'll never give me any information.

213
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:47,761
And that will be the end of my career.

214
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:51,765
Why would I risk my entire career
just to write this one article?

215
00:14:52,266 --> 00:14:53,726
Don't you think I'm out of my mind?

216
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:56,186
Gosh, this is seriously crazy.

217
00:14:59,106 --> 00:15:02,776
I want you to check
if Jo Seong-dae got orders from Kim Gi-tae

218
00:15:02,860 --> 00:15:06,614
and if Kim Gi-tae knew about Oh Jong-tae.

219
00:15:06,697 --> 00:15:09,116
Are you kidding me?

220
00:15:09,199 --> 00:15:12,411
Like I just said, this is completely nuts.

221
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:15,539
-Make sure you check it for me.
-Detective Oh.

222
00:15:15,623 --> 00:15:16,624
Detective Oh!

223
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:21,503
Like you said,
Lee Dae-cheol really seems to be innocent.

224
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:25,883
But the case happened too long ago,
so we don't have conclusive evidence.

225
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:30,054
Things would become a lot easier
if someone confesses the truth.

226
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:33,849
Why don't you help me, sir?

227
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,392
What do I need to help you with?

228
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:36,518
Jo Seong-dae.

229
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:40,731
I know you guys are close.
Didn't he tell you anything?

230
00:15:41,482 --> 00:15:43,275
He must not have told you

231
00:15:43,359 --> 00:15:46,195
that he killed Park Gun-ho
and that he tried to kill me, too.

232
00:15:47,571 --> 00:15:49,907
The cops are trying to find out
who's behind him.

233
00:15:49,990 --> 00:15:52,743
And I got to meet him

234
00:15:52,826 --> 00:15:55,204
because of you.

235
00:15:55,287 --> 00:15:57,581
-Jo Seong-dae?
-Yes, Jo Seong-dae.

236
00:15:58,457 --> 00:15:59,833
Who is that person?

237
00:15:59,917 --> 00:16:01,794
You sent him to pick me up.

238
00:16:02,753 --> 00:16:07,967
Oh, I asked my nephew to pick you up.

239
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:10,302
But I guess he sent that guy instead
because he was busy.

240
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:15,307
I'll ask my nephew
what kind of person he is.

241
00:16:16,725 --> 00:16:19,019
-Sir.
-I didn't have any ulterior motives

242
00:16:19,103 --> 00:16:20,938
when I told you about
Lee Dae-cheol's innocence.

243
00:16:21,021 --> 00:16:24,483
No, I'll be honest.
There's a reason why I told you.

244
00:16:24,566 --> 00:16:28,821
Once my trial begins,
you'll be asked to speak as a witness.

245
00:16:28,904 --> 00:16:32,950
And I wanted to make sure my witness
had a positive image of me.

246
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:34,410
That's all.

247
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:41,208
If you figured out the culprit,

248
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:44,211
shouldn't you have told me about it first?

249
00:16:44,294 --> 00:16:47,297
I still need to investigate it a bit more.

250
00:16:47,381 --> 00:16:49,508
Who exactly are you investigating?

251
00:16:49,591 --> 00:16:53,679
It's not the person you thought it was.

252
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:59,059
But your ultimate goal
is the person I'm thinking about, right?

253
00:17:02,813 --> 00:17:04,064
If you want,

254
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:06,483
I can stop here.

255
00:17:13,657 --> 00:17:16,118
Detective Kang, I've never been

256
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:18,704
in charge of a retrial before,
and to be honest,

257
00:17:19,705 --> 00:17:21,165
I don't think I can do it.

258
00:17:21,248 --> 00:17:24,251
On top of that,
he's going to get executed soon.

259
00:17:24,334 --> 00:17:27,463
The judiciary won't accept
such a sensitive issue.

260
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:32,634
Plus, I'm too cowardly
to take on big cases like this.

261
00:17:33,260 --> 00:17:34,595
Mr. So.

262
00:17:35,179 --> 00:17:38,640
I arrested Lee Dae-cheol myself.

263
00:17:39,558 --> 00:17:43,479
The detective who arrested the culprit
is asking for a retrial

264
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:45,522
to prove the culprit's innocence.

265
00:17:46,607 --> 00:17:51,278
Right now,
I'm practically cutting my own throat.

266
00:17:52,237 --> 00:17:53,697
It's crazy.

267
00:17:55,824 --> 00:17:58,035
-So why are you doing this?
-Nothing will happen

268
00:17:58,118 --> 00:18:00,454
if I stay quiet. I know that.

269
00:18:00,537 --> 00:18:03,248
But if I don't do anything,

270
00:18:05,084 --> 00:18:06,627
no one will speak the truth.

271
00:18:14,718 --> 00:18:17,262
Drawings are very different from photos.

272
00:18:17,971 --> 00:18:19,890
Drawings hold emotions.

273
00:18:20,557 --> 00:18:22,893
That's because one person draws the other.

274
00:18:24,311 --> 00:18:25,604
What do you see in me?

275
00:18:27,272 --> 00:18:28,357
Anger?

276
00:18:29,274 --> 00:18:31,860
You seem very angry at something.

277
00:18:32,986 --> 00:18:34,822
Anyway, you look a bit sad.

278
00:19:02,432 --> 00:19:05,769
I'll put the lawyer on the phone.
You can talk to him.

279
00:19:05,853 --> 00:19:07,020
Just a second.

280
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:09,606
-It's Ko Jun-seop.
-Oh, okay.

281
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:14,403
Hello. I'm So Jae-seop, a lawyer.

282
00:19:18,407 --> 00:19:21,034
Yoon Ji-seon's friend told us that.

283
00:19:22,202 --> 00:19:24,580
How many witnesses do we have?

284
00:19:25,414 --> 00:19:28,333
-Ko Jun-seop.
-Yoon Ji-seon's friend.

285
00:19:56,320 --> 00:20:00,157
NOVEMBER 3, 2015, 9:18:27 P.M.
MAN LEAVES ROOM

286
00:20:00,240 --> 00:20:03,035
NOVEMBER 3, 2015, 1:12:44 A.M.
UNKNOWN OBJECT APPEARS

287
00:20:06,288 --> 00:20:09,708
No matter how hard I try,
the result doesn't change.

288
00:20:12,419 --> 00:20:15,380
There's no evidence to prove
that Oh Jong-tae is the culprit.

289
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:18,342
And there's no evidence to prove
that Lee Dae-cheol is innocent.

290
00:20:19,551 --> 00:20:24,097
Retrials require a lot trickier
than ordinary trials.

291
00:20:25,807 --> 00:20:26,975
This won't work.

292
00:20:27,517 --> 00:20:28,352
We have a witness.

293
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:29,895
Ko Jun-seop?

294
00:20:29,978 --> 00:20:33,440
But he didn't witness the murder.

295
00:20:33,523 --> 00:20:34,942
-What about a cop?
-A cop?

296
00:20:37,027 --> 00:20:41,031
The witness that judges trust the most
is the detective who was in charge.

297
00:20:41,114 --> 00:20:43,283
What if that detective testifies in court?

298
00:20:45,494 --> 00:20:49,748
You want me to jump into the fiery pit
with a gasoline tank?

299
00:20:54,253 --> 00:20:55,254
Okay, sure.

300
00:20:57,297 --> 00:21:00,759
Do-chang is busy
chasing after Joo Dong-pal now.

301
00:21:00,842 --> 00:21:02,261
That's just for show.

302
00:21:02,344 --> 00:21:05,681
From what I know,
he's reinvestigating Lee Dae-cheol's case.

303
00:21:06,223 --> 00:21:08,600
-Why?
-You know him.

304
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:10,811
Once he believes something is right,

305
00:21:10,894 --> 00:21:13,146
he pushes forward
without thinking about the consequences.

306
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:16,066
He's changed a lot.
He's not like how he was in the past.

307
00:21:16,733 --> 00:21:21,905
You know I'm currently
inspecting Detective Kang, right?

308
00:21:22,614 --> 00:21:24,700
He recently came to see me.

309
00:21:24,783 --> 00:21:27,452
"I wonder why that happened
to that person back then.

310
00:21:27,536 --> 00:21:29,329
I thought it was a coincidence.

311
00:21:29,413 --> 00:21:33,083
But now, why does it seem like
that person had an ulterior motive?"

312
00:21:33,166 --> 00:21:36,712
Sooner or later, I might have to do my job

313
00:21:36,795 --> 00:21:39,172
and do something unfortunate
to a good friend of mine.

314
00:21:39,256 --> 00:21:43,343
What does he mean by "back then"?

315
00:21:43,427 --> 00:21:45,512
He's talking about that time
when I lost the weapon

316
00:21:46,138 --> 00:21:49,224
and you found it
and brought it back for me.

317
00:21:49,766 --> 00:21:51,935
And he said he might have to do
something unfortunate

318
00:21:52,019 --> 00:21:54,229
because he knows he'll have to open up
about what happened

319
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:58,150
once he begins
reinvestigating Lee Dae-cheol's case.

320
00:21:58,775 --> 00:22:00,652
If my mistake goes public,

321
00:22:00,736 --> 00:22:03,447
it'll taint my career.

322
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:06,867
And people will also question you

323
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:09,578
for having found the weapon.

324
00:22:14,499 --> 00:22:17,586
What do cops normally do
if they retire early?

325
00:22:18,086 --> 00:22:19,087
Illegal detectives?

326
00:22:20,088 --> 00:22:21,465
That job is too messy.

327
00:22:22,132 --> 00:22:23,008
Private bodyguards?

328
00:22:23,842 --> 00:22:25,886
But that requires a lot of stamina.

329
00:22:27,429 --> 00:22:28,680
You're too old for that.

330
00:22:29,890 --> 00:22:30,974
My gosh.

331
00:22:32,184 --> 00:22:33,727
Age doesn't matter.

332
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:37,272
I'll hire someone young
and make him work for me instead.

333
00:22:37,355 --> 00:22:39,024
-Who?
-There's this guy.

334
00:22:39,107 --> 00:22:40,692
He threw me into the fiery pit.

335
00:22:40,776 --> 00:22:45,530
But rest assured.
I'll take him with me no matter what.

336
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:09,721
Yoon Sang-mi?

337
00:23:10,764 --> 00:23:11,848
At this hour? Why?

338
00:23:12,724 --> 00:23:15,727
She came by herself? For what?
Whom did she meet?

339
00:23:25,153 --> 00:23:27,030
Don't answer the phone.
Just hold it for me.

340
00:23:32,744 --> 00:23:33,703
CHIEF MOON SANG-BEOM

341
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:46,591
Give me that.

342
00:23:50,178 --> 00:23:55,058
I'm… I'm chasing a culprit right now.

343
00:23:55,142 --> 00:23:57,185
Why did you have to call me now?

344
00:23:57,269 --> 00:24:01,106
Hey! Stop right there! You darn punk!

345
00:24:05,068 --> 00:24:06,403
Let's go catch Joo Dong-pal.

346
00:24:06,486 --> 00:24:08,280
It's time to arrest him now.
Start the car.

347
00:24:11,324 --> 00:24:12,325
Who is it?

348
00:24:12,909 --> 00:24:14,703
Hey, Yu-na. It's me.

349
00:24:16,121 --> 00:24:19,583
What's wrong?
Couldn't you find a place to sleep again?

350
00:24:20,709 --> 00:24:22,210
You can pay first.

351
00:24:22,294 --> 00:24:23,587
Crazy bitch.

352
00:24:27,424 --> 00:24:29,426
You told the cops about me, didn't you?

353
00:24:33,763 --> 00:24:35,307
Hey!

354
00:24:38,351 --> 00:24:41,104
-What's up?
-Hong-du is going to kill me.

355
00:24:41,688 --> 00:24:43,940
-Why would he kill you?
-Because I fell for that cop

356
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:45,775
and gave him Hong-du's number.

357
00:24:45,859 --> 00:24:48,278
Eun-hye, please help me.

358
00:24:48,361 --> 00:24:49,613
Where are you right now?

359
00:24:49,696 --> 00:24:52,199
You know that place where… That place…

360
00:24:52,282 --> 00:24:54,326
Oh, the empty house
where I held my birthday party.

361
00:24:54,409 --> 00:24:56,411
Hong-du will find me soon.

362
00:24:56,494 --> 00:24:58,622
Can you stay with me until he comes

363
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:00,707
and convince him to forgive me?

364
00:25:00,790 --> 00:25:03,960
If I'm here all by myself,
he'll beat me to death.

365
00:25:04,044 --> 00:25:06,671
I was only trying to help you.
That's why this happened.

366
00:25:06,755 --> 00:25:08,548
Eun-hye, please.

367
00:25:09,257 --> 00:25:10,884
Okay, wait there.

368
00:25:16,014 --> 00:25:17,390
Where are you going?

369
00:25:18,642 --> 00:25:22,103
Detective Kang told me
not to let you leave at night.

370
00:25:22,187 --> 00:25:23,772
I'm not locked up in jail.

371
00:25:23,855 --> 00:25:26,233
Do you plan not to come back?

372
00:25:32,447 --> 00:25:34,407
Let's say you secretly ran away.

373
00:25:35,075 --> 00:25:36,993
That will work best for both of us.

374
00:26:08,358 --> 00:26:10,110
-Did you guys eat?
-Yes.

375
00:26:10,193 --> 00:26:11,319
Let's do this.

376
00:26:12,112 --> 00:26:13,738
Where is Joo Dong-pal?

377
00:26:13,822 --> 00:26:15,282
He'll show up soon.

378
00:26:15,365 --> 00:26:17,367
He's crazy about women.

379
00:26:18,243 --> 00:26:21,621
He probably had a few drinks.
He'll show up in front of her house soon.

380
00:26:21,705 --> 00:26:24,374
If it's so easy to catch him,
why did you have to call us here?

381
00:26:24,457 --> 00:26:27,836
Are you nuts? Why would I catch him alone?
I can't stand seeing you guys slack off.

382
00:26:29,546 --> 00:26:31,339
-He's here.
-There he is.

383
00:26:34,384 --> 00:26:36,303
Let's get going. Go.

384
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:44,561
Who are those guys?

385
00:26:45,270 --> 00:26:47,063
I think they're from Gwangju.

386
00:26:47,147 --> 00:26:48,231
Damn it.

387
00:26:48,815 --> 00:26:50,150
Joo Dong-pal!

388
00:26:51,484 --> 00:26:52,861
-Run.
-Darn it.

389
00:26:53,403 --> 00:26:54,738
-You punk!
-Hey!

390
00:26:54,821 --> 00:26:55,780
Stop right there!

391
00:26:55,864 --> 00:26:56,948
Damn it.

392
00:26:57,032 --> 00:26:59,993
-Come here, you punk!
-Get over here!

393
00:27:00,076 --> 00:27:01,995
-Move!
-Hey, don't push!

394
00:27:02,078 --> 00:27:03,830
-Get out of my way!
-Hey!

395
00:27:03,913 --> 00:27:05,832
Let me through!

396
00:27:05,915 --> 00:27:07,751
-Hey!
-Go get him!

397
00:27:07,834 --> 00:27:10,003
-Get over here!
-Hey!

398
00:27:10,086 --> 00:27:12,339
-Go!
-Catch him!

399
00:27:23,224 --> 00:27:24,351
You punk!

400
00:27:24,434 --> 00:27:25,894
Get over here!

401
00:27:25,977 --> 00:27:27,520
My gosh, move!

402
00:27:28,021 --> 00:27:29,689
Where do you think you're going?

403
00:27:36,946 --> 00:27:38,698
Ji-hyeok!

404
00:27:39,866 --> 00:27:41,242
Ji-hyeok!

405
00:27:41,868 --> 00:27:45,830
Ji-hyeok!

406
00:27:46,331 --> 00:27:48,291
Catch him for me!

407
00:27:48,375 --> 00:27:49,626
Come here!

408
00:27:49,709 --> 00:27:51,252
-Stop!
-You punk!

409
00:27:51,336 --> 00:27:53,838
-Get out of my way!
-Let go of me!

410
00:27:53,922 --> 00:27:55,673
-Move!
-Go!

411
00:27:56,841 --> 00:27:59,636
-Hey, move!
-Darn you!

412
00:27:59,719 --> 00:28:01,054
Catch him!

413
00:28:01,137 --> 00:28:03,306
-Get over here!
-Go!

414
00:28:19,114 --> 00:28:21,783
-Darn it!
-Go get him!

415
00:28:22,283 --> 00:28:23,660
My gosh.

416
00:28:23,743 --> 00:28:25,703
-Hey!
-Come here, you punk!

417
00:28:29,541 --> 00:28:31,793
-Go!
-I got him!

418
00:28:37,090 --> 00:28:38,675
Get out of my way!

419
00:28:40,427 --> 00:28:41,803
Get off me!

420
00:28:41,886 --> 00:28:44,264
-Move!
-My gosh!

421
00:28:44,347 --> 00:28:46,182
-Darn it!
-Where is he?

422
00:28:46,266 --> 00:28:48,268
-He's not here!
-Get him!

423
00:28:48,351 --> 00:28:49,436
Stop right there!

424
00:28:50,186 --> 00:28:51,521
My gosh!

425
00:28:51,604 --> 00:28:53,189
Hey, you darn punk!

426
00:28:53,273 --> 00:28:54,524
Come here!

427
00:28:54,607 --> 00:28:55,608
My gosh!

428
00:28:55,692 --> 00:28:58,153
Come over here!

429
00:28:58,695 --> 00:29:00,029
Damn it!

430
00:29:01,072 --> 00:29:02,323
I caught him.

431
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:03,867
My goodness.

432
00:29:05,410 --> 00:29:06,578
My gosh.

433
00:29:07,370 --> 00:29:08,788
Where did it go?

434
00:29:10,331 --> 00:29:11,624
-Move.
-Wait.

435
00:29:11,708 --> 00:29:14,043
-Okay, wait.
-Jae-hong!

436
00:29:15,462 --> 00:29:18,047
-Damn it!
-There we go!

437
00:29:18,131 --> 00:29:19,132
I got him.

438
00:29:23,219 --> 00:29:24,554
Have a safe trip back.

439
00:29:25,096 --> 00:29:26,639
That's enough.

440
00:29:26,723 --> 00:29:29,184
Come on. Get up.

441
00:29:29,267 --> 00:29:31,686
-We caught him.
-My gosh.

442
00:29:35,231 --> 00:29:38,568
Gosh, you guys came from so far away.

443
00:29:38,651 --> 00:29:42,322
Anyway, thank you so much
for your cooperation.

444
00:29:42,405 --> 00:29:44,240
My goodness, this is great.

445
00:29:45,909 --> 00:29:48,036
-Let's go.
-Great work, guys.

446
00:29:48,119 --> 00:29:49,662
You guys should eat.

447
00:29:49,746 --> 00:29:50,747
Damn it.

448
00:29:54,125 --> 00:29:55,293
Great job.

449
00:29:55,376 --> 00:29:56,628
Nice job, Jae-hong!

450
00:30:55,812 --> 00:30:57,021
What are you doing here?

451
00:30:58,606 --> 00:30:59,774
Did you call her?

452
00:31:02,151 --> 00:31:05,780
Listen. I hate that brat.
She attracts cops.

453
00:31:06,447 --> 00:31:10,159
What were you trying to do with her?

454
00:31:10,243 --> 00:31:11,911
-Aren't you going to answer me?
-Stop.

455
00:31:14,998 --> 00:31:17,792
Hey, I get angry just by looking at you.

456
00:31:17,876 --> 00:31:18,877
Just get lost.

457
00:31:18,960 --> 00:31:21,504
I asked her to do everything.
Hit me instead.

458
00:31:22,338 --> 00:31:24,382
You have an amazing friend.

459
00:31:24,924 --> 00:31:26,551
You're very loyal.

460
00:31:27,844 --> 00:31:30,096
Hey, you two.
Take her somewhere and teach her a lesson.

461
00:31:30,805 --> 00:31:32,515
She gave me this scar on my nose.

462
00:31:32,599 --> 00:31:34,350
Make sure you beat her to a pulp.

463
00:31:34,434 --> 00:31:35,310
Eun-hye.

464
00:31:35,393 --> 00:31:36,936
-Stop it.
-Please.

465
00:31:37,020 --> 00:31:39,772
Get her out of my sight.

466
00:31:39,856 --> 00:31:40,940
I said stop it!

467
00:31:41,024 --> 00:31:42,609
Take her out, you punks!

468
00:31:42,692 --> 00:31:43,985
Let me go!

469
00:31:44,068 --> 00:31:45,820
This is all because of you!

470
00:32:00,585 --> 00:32:01,586
Hey, let her go.

471
00:32:02,378 --> 00:32:03,963
I said let her go.

472
00:32:28,446 --> 00:32:32,200
I want you to take
four more guys with you.

473
00:32:32,283 --> 00:32:34,285
It'll be lonely
if you go to jail all alone.

474
00:32:35,328 --> 00:32:38,831
Just pick four people
who aren't that close to you.

475
00:32:39,415 --> 00:32:41,501
Teams One and Two! Attention!

476
00:32:41,584 --> 00:32:42,835
At ease, guys.

477
00:32:45,797 --> 00:32:46,965
Good work.

478
00:32:50,259 --> 00:32:51,636
Which one of you cuffed this guy?

479
00:32:52,220 --> 00:32:53,930
It was Jae-hong.

480
00:32:54,013 --> 00:32:57,767
Gosh, I had no idea he could be so fast.
He was as fast as lightning.

481
00:32:57,850 --> 00:32:59,102
You should've seen him, sir.

482
00:32:59,185 --> 00:33:03,022
He's normally very slow.
But whenever he sees a culprit,

483
00:33:03,106 --> 00:33:04,440
he turns into Usain Bolt.

484
00:33:04,524 --> 00:33:06,734
He was born to be a detective.

485
00:33:06,818 --> 00:33:08,403
What's wrong with you guys?

486
00:33:08,486 --> 00:33:10,613
Don't be too humble.

487
00:33:11,322 --> 00:33:12,824
You know my two principles, right?

488
00:33:12,907 --> 00:33:15,451
No matter what happens,

489
00:33:15,535 --> 00:33:17,662
I will pick out those who blame others
for their faults.

490
00:33:17,745 --> 00:33:19,455
And I will always make sure

491
00:33:19,539 --> 00:33:22,834
to reward people
who contributed to doing the right thing.

492
00:33:25,294 --> 00:33:28,006
I didn't catch him by myself.

493
00:33:28,089 --> 00:33:30,925
You're right.
Catching culprits requires teamwork.

494
00:33:31,426 --> 00:33:34,721
You guys really did well this time.

495
00:33:34,804 --> 00:33:37,306
I can really count on Team Two.

496
00:33:38,182 --> 00:33:39,142
Team Two!

497
00:33:42,770 --> 00:33:43,604
Good job.

498
00:33:49,402 --> 00:33:51,070
What if she dies?

499
00:33:51,154 --> 00:33:53,239
Don't worry. She'll wake up soon.

500
00:33:53,322 --> 00:33:55,158
Hong-du, what about me?

501
00:33:56,617 --> 00:33:57,660
You're a great actress.

502
00:33:57,744 --> 00:34:00,538
I know, right? Does this mean we're even?

503
00:34:03,082 --> 00:34:05,501
You'd better not lie to me. I'll kill you.

504
00:34:05,585 --> 00:34:08,713
Of course, I won't.
Why would you even say that?

505
00:34:50,421 --> 00:34:52,381
Let's say you secretly ran away.

506
00:34:52,465 --> 00:34:54,383
That will work best for both of us.

507
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:16,072
-Raise your glasses.
-Okay.

508
00:35:16,697 --> 00:35:18,407
Cheers to Violent Crimes Unit Team Two!

