You're going to be on TV, Do-chang.

766
00:50:50,422 --> 00:50:53,425
A death-row convict is raising an issue
for having filed for a retrial.

767
00:50:53,508 --> 00:50:56,678
Let's hear about the details
from the reporter in charge.

768
00:50:56,762 --> 00:50:59,347
Prior to the execution
that hasn't been carried out in 20 years,

769
00:50:59,431 --> 00:51:02,726
I heard one of the death-row convicts
filed for a retrial. Who is that?

770
00:51:02,809 --> 00:51:06,104
He's Lee Dae-cheol, a death-row convict
who killed a female college student

771
00:51:06,188 --> 00:51:08,523
and a police detective five years ago.

772
00:51:08,607 --> 00:51:11,193
Why is he asking for a retrial?

773
00:51:11,276 --> 00:51:15,030
Because he thinks the investigation
was carried out poorly and coercively.

774
00:51:15,113 --> 00:51:18,241
I went to Incheon Seobu Police Station
and met the detective

775
00:51:18,325 --> 00:51:20,368
who investigated the case
and arrested Lee Dae-cheol.

776
00:51:20,452 --> 00:51:22,579
He was extremely agitated.

777
00:51:22,662 --> 00:51:25,207
Let's take a look at the footage
before I go into further detail.

778
00:51:28,460 --> 00:51:31,171
Detective Kang Do-chang.

779
00:51:31,254 --> 00:51:34,341
Are you the detective who was in charge
of Lee Dae-cheol's case five years ago?

780
00:51:34,424 --> 00:51:36,092
Yes, what do you want?

781
00:51:36,176 --> 00:51:37,594
-Is that you?
-Do you know that…

782
00:51:38,178 --> 00:51:39,179
-Sir, wait.
-Yes.

783
00:51:39,262 --> 00:51:41,890
Did you know
that Lee Dae-cheol filed for a retrial?

784
00:51:41,973 --> 00:51:45,060
There's nothing he can't do
now that he's about to get executed.

785
00:51:45,143 --> 00:51:47,312
He's just fighting for his life.

786
00:51:47,395 --> 00:51:49,481
Wait, sir.

787
00:51:49,564 --> 00:51:52,484
Did you also know that the evangelist
who recently committed suicide

788
00:51:52,567 --> 00:51:54,194
claimed that Lee Dae-cheol is innocent?

789
00:51:54,277 --> 00:51:56,947
That happened before
the order of execution was made.

790
00:51:57,030 --> 00:51:59,616
So he might not be doing this
to avoid getting executed.

791
00:51:59,699 --> 00:52:02,828
What matters is that he put on a show.
Where are you from?

792
00:52:03,328 --> 00:52:05,664
Detective Kang, does that mean

793
00:52:05,747 --> 00:52:09,167
you don't believe
what Lee Dae-cheol is saying?

794
00:52:09,251 --> 00:52:13,213
What kind of detective would think
the guy he arrested is actually innocent?

795
00:52:13,296 --> 00:52:14,548
I heard he filed for a retrial

796
00:52:14,631 --> 00:52:16,716
because the investigation
was carried out poorly.

797
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:18,301
What do you think about that?

798
00:52:18,385 --> 00:52:20,554
Let's say the police did a poor job.

799
00:52:21,054 --> 00:52:23,598
But then, what about the judge
and prosecution?

800
00:52:23,682 --> 00:52:28,019
They gave him a death sentence
because the evidence was loud and clear.

801
00:52:28,103 --> 00:52:31,356
I'm busy, okay? Why the fuck are you here?

802
00:52:31,439 --> 00:52:34,526
-Detective Kang.
-That asshole is just fucking around.

803
00:52:34,609 --> 00:52:36,027
That damn bastard.

804
00:52:36,111 --> 00:52:37,362
Stop filming me, you asshole!

805
00:52:37,445 --> 00:52:41,992
Hey, why would you swear
in front of the camera?

806
00:52:42,075 --> 00:52:44,995
That reporter got me all riled up.
Do you know what he said…

807
00:52:45,078 --> 00:52:49,040
-My gosh.
-It looks like there's another reason.

808
00:52:49,124 --> 00:52:51,334
The detective reacted
very sensitively to the issue.

809
00:52:51,418 --> 00:52:53,962
Yes, you'll understand why

810
00:52:54,045 --> 00:52:56,548
-once you watch the next interview.
-Okay.

811
00:52:56,631 --> 00:53:00,719
It was very difficult, but we managed
to meet an acquaintance of the victim.

812
00:53:00,802 --> 00:53:02,012
Let's take a look.

813
00:53:03,096 --> 00:53:07,350
You were dating Yoon Ji-seon
five years ago before she died?

814
00:53:07,434 --> 00:53:08,935
-Yes.
-After the incident,

815
00:53:09,019 --> 00:53:10,478
did the cops investigate you?

816
00:53:11,062 --> 00:53:12,647
No, not at all.

817
00:53:12,731 --> 00:53:14,524
Didn't they even summon you
for a statement?

818
00:53:15,233 --> 00:53:18,987
If you were the victim's boyfriend,
that would make you the key suspect.

819
00:53:19,070 --> 00:53:20,530
Why didn't they investigate you?

820
00:53:20,614 --> 00:53:24,576
I don't know. I'm sure they had a reason.
But it's still hard for me to understand.

821
00:53:24,659 --> 00:53:27,913
Whatever the case,
do you think there was a problem

822
00:53:27,996 --> 00:53:29,539
with the police investigation?

823
00:53:30,206 --> 00:53:34,252
Yes, that's right.
I honestly don't trust the police.

824
00:53:34,336 --> 00:53:35,503
As you can see,

825
00:53:35,587 --> 00:53:38,048
-Who is that guy?
-he thinks the primary investigation…

826
00:53:38,131 --> 00:53:40,800
-I don't know.
-Why don't you know?

827
00:53:40,884 --> 00:53:43,678
I wasn't in charge
of carrying out the primary investigation

828
00:53:43,762 --> 00:53:45,931
regarding Yoon Ji-seon's death.

829
00:53:46,014 --> 00:53:49,476
The late Detective Jang Jin-su
and Captain Nam Guk-hyeon were in charge.

830
00:53:49,559 --> 00:53:51,645
He even asked the reporter

831
00:53:51,728 --> 00:53:54,689
to ask the police and prosecution
for a proper investigation

832
00:53:54,773 --> 00:53:58,109
so that Yoon Ji-seon will be able
to rest in peace.

833
00:53:58,193 --> 00:53:59,778
Will this change the judge's mind?

834
00:54:00,987 --> 00:54:03,782
I looked into the judge who's in charge.
He won't be easy to convince.

835
00:54:03,865 --> 00:54:07,118
His bar score and training institute
test results were in the top ten percent.

836
00:54:07,202 --> 00:54:11,039
Judges live with their reputation
throughout their entire career.

837
00:54:11,665 --> 00:54:14,000
He's too perfect. He won't listen to us.

838
00:54:15,043 --> 00:54:16,628
I'm sure he'll listen to God.

839
00:54:18,004 --> 00:54:20,507
The members of the Justice
and Peace Committee

840
00:54:20,590 --> 00:54:22,258
of the Catholic Church

841
00:54:22,342 --> 00:54:25,637
have gathered in front
of the Supreme Court

842
00:54:25,720 --> 00:54:29,349
to hold a silent protest
for the abolishment of the death penalty

843
00:54:29,432 --> 00:54:31,226
and the approval
of Lee Dae-cheol's retrial.

844
00:54:46,658 --> 00:54:49,244
Hello, Chief Administrative Officer.
It's me.

845
00:54:52,122 --> 00:54:53,623
I have a favor to ask.

846
00:54:54,124 --> 00:54:56,334
Here's breaking news.

847
00:54:56,418 --> 00:55:00,171
Today at noon, the Supreme Court accepted
Lee Dae-cheol's request for a retrial

848
00:55:00,255 --> 00:55:03,758
and asked the Seoul High Court
to carry out the procedure.

849
00:55:03,842 --> 00:55:07,804
Many people are curious to see
how the first retrial will turn out

850
00:55:07,887 --> 00:55:11,141
before the execution takes place
for the first time in 20 years.

851
00:55:14,019 --> 00:55:15,729
Did you hear the news?

852
00:55:15,812 --> 00:55:17,272
We just did the impossible.

853
00:55:17,355 --> 00:55:19,983
Getting approval for a retrial isn't easy

854
00:55:20,066 --> 00:55:21,776
especially when he's waiting
to get executed.

855
00:55:21,860 --> 00:55:24,029
Detective Kang, you'd make a great actor.

856
00:55:24,112 --> 00:55:26,281
Your acting wasn't awkward at all.

857
00:55:27,198 --> 00:55:29,784
We're actually going to get a job
at a movie production company

858
00:55:29,868 --> 00:55:31,286
once we're done with this.

859
00:55:31,369 --> 00:55:32,495
Why me?

860
00:55:32,579 --> 00:55:36,458
I noticed this time around
that you're great when it comes to fraud.

861
00:55:36,541 --> 00:55:38,376
You can write scripts, and I'll act.

862
00:55:38,460 --> 00:55:40,295
Don't you think it'll do great?

863
00:55:40,378 --> 00:55:42,964
You can be the villain.
A villain who swears very well.

864
00:55:43,048 --> 00:55:45,717
No, I won't be a good villain.
I'm fit to play a detective.

865
00:55:45,800 --> 00:55:47,510
Many detectives are like villains.

866
00:55:48,595 --> 00:55:51,222
Is that how you think of me?

867
00:55:51,306 --> 00:55:54,809
No, I'm just talking about your looks.

868
00:55:55,977 --> 00:55:57,520
What's wrong with how I look?

869
00:55:57,604 --> 00:55:59,647
You're the one
who looks like a troublemaker.

870
00:55:59,731 --> 00:56:01,566
You totally look like a con-artist.

871
00:56:01,649 --> 00:56:03,443
Don't smile, you punk.

872
00:56:03,526 --> 00:56:08,073
My gosh. We didn't win the trial yet.

873
00:56:08,156 --> 00:56:09,365
This is just the beginning.

874
00:56:09,449 --> 00:56:13,369
At least it's something.
Plus, the public seems to support us.

875
00:56:13,453 --> 00:56:14,871
Isn't this a decent start?

876
00:56:14,954 --> 00:56:17,248
If I were the judge in charge,

877
00:56:17,332 --> 00:56:20,251
I wouldn't have accepted the retrial.

878
00:56:21,127 --> 00:56:24,005
He just agreed to do it
due to the public sentiment.

879
00:56:24,089 --> 00:56:27,509
The evidence we handed in isn't enough
even in my point of view.

880
00:56:27,592 --> 00:56:29,511
We'll slowly--

881
00:56:29,594 --> 00:56:31,221
You know we don't have time.

882
00:56:31,846 --> 00:56:35,141
First, we need to decide
how we're going to prepare for the trial.

883
00:56:36,142 --> 00:56:40,814
Instead of focusing on Detective Jang,
I'm going to focus more on Yoon Ji-seon.

884
00:56:40,897 --> 00:56:43,274
If we can prove that he didn't kill her,

885
00:56:43,358 --> 00:56:45,985
we can stop him from getting executed.

886
00:56:46,069 --> 00:56:47,612
And most importantly,

887
00:56:47,695 --> 00:56:51,783
we need to prove that the investigation
wasn't carried out properly back then.

888
00:56:51,866 --> 00:56:54,953
We need to check everything the cops hid,
their irregularities, coercion,

889
00:56:55,036 --> 00:56:57,288
and how that led to a poor investigation.

890
00:56:58,373 --> 00:57:01,584
You're in full charge of that.

891
00:57:01,668 --> 00:57:02,669
You know that, right?

892
00:57:03,753 --> 00:57:05,421
I'll do everything I can.

893
00:57:05,505 --> 00:57:06,965
We must win this case no matter what.

894
00:57:11,386 --> 00:57:14,097
Did you also agree to this retrial?

895
00:57:14,180 --> 00:57:16,516
They will announce
how the cabinet will be reshuffled soon.

896
00:57:16,599 --> 00:57:19,727
I don't want to risk anything
as soon as my term begins.

897
00:57:19,811 --> 00:57:21,688
I should get it over with before that.

898
00:57:22,814 --> 00:57:25,525
The opposition party is already
getting ready for a hearing.

899
00:57:25,608 --> 00:57:29,320
It's obvious that they'll raise an issue
about my relationship with Jong-tae.

900
00:57:30,947 --> 00:57:35,535
You should meet him one more time
and make him promise to keep quiet.

901
00:57:37,162 --> 00:57:38,580
To be honest,

902
00:57:39,414 --> 00:57:40,623
I don't trust him.

903
00:57:41,499 --> 00:57:43,376
Okay, I'll take care of it.

904
00:57:44,377 --> 00:57:46,337
Just let me know what you want.

905
00:57:46,421 --> 00:57:48,548
You just want me to stay quiet, right?

906
00:57:49,340 --> 00:57:51,426
If you need me to do anything,

907
00:57:52,260 --> 00:57:53,428
give me a script.

908
00:57:54,304 --> 00:57:58,516
I'll memorize every single word
and say exactly what you ask me to say.

909
00:57:58,600 --> 00:58:01,394
I'll let you know once there's a hearing.

910
00:58:02,645 --> 00:58:05,190
By any chance, did Assemblyman Yoo

911
00:58:05,273 --> 00:58:08,776
take part in making a decision
for the retrial?

912
00:58:09,986 --> 00:58:11,362
Why do you want to know?

913
00:58:11,946 --> 00:58:13,239
I'm just curious.

914
00:58:13,323 --> 00:58:16,367
The justice department made that decision
due to the public sentiment.

915
00:58:18,661 --> 00:58:23,458
I feel like someone powerful
must've given some advice.

916
00:58:24,667 --> 00:58:27,670
The current Minister of Justice
doesn't have a lot of power left.

917
00:58:27,754 --> 00:58:32,592
Assemblyman Yoo Jeong-ryeol
probably has a lot more power right now.

918
00:58:32,675 --> 00:58:35,512
So the person who had enough power
to make that decision would be…

919
00:58:38,515 --> 00:58:41,184
I don't understand
why you're so curious about that.

920
00:58:41,768 --> 00:58:43,853
But I know one thing for sure.

921
00:58:44,437 --> 00:58:49,234
The person must be closed by the one
who opened it.

922
00:58:53,863 --> 00:58:56,324
Anyway, let's do what we can
for each other

923
00:58:57,325 --> 00:58:59,494
and make sure we don't cause any harm.

924
00:59:05,333 --> 00:59:07,335
I don't get it.

925
00:59:08,503 --> 00:59:10,922
How could they accept
his request for a retrial?

926
00:59:11,965 --> 00:59:15,176
Who's behind Lee Dae-cheol?

927
00:59:16,219 --> 00:59:17,053
I don't know.

928
00:59:18,638 --> 00:59:19,889
I'm quite curious myself.

929
00:59:20,598 --> 00:59:22,892
That guy has absolutely nothing.

930
00:59:23,601 --> 00:59:27,438
It looks like he wrote letters
to lots of different people in jail.

931
00:59:27,522 --> 00:59:30,316
That's probably why the Catholic Church
is holding a protest.

932
00:59:31,859 --> 00:59:34,237
Now that the court has decided
to hold a retrial,

933
00:59:34,904 --> 00:59:36,823
there's nothing we can do to turn it back.

934
00:59:36,906 --> 00:59:41,578
Us three are the only ones
who were involved in Lee Dae-cheol's case.

935
00:59:42,161 --> 00:59:44,163
I can take care of myself.

936
00:59:44,247 --> 00:59:48,042
Meanwhile, I want you guys
to make sure you keep your mouths shut.

937
00:59:48,126 --> 00:59:51,546
No matter how much a reporter follows you,
don't let them interview you.

938
00:59:52,797 --> 00:59:56,718
If the lawyer asks you for evidence,
don't give them anything.

939
00:59:56,801 --> 00:59:58,636
There's nothing left anyway.

940
00:59:59,345 --> 01:00:02,557
The court might summon you.
Don't even think of going there.

941
01:00:02,640 --> 01:00:05,476
You won't be breaking any laws
by not going. Do you understand?

942
01:00:05,560 --> 01:00:07,103
Yes, sir.

943
01:00:08,438 --> 01:00:09,439
If

944
01:00:10,481 --> 01:00:12,567
the retrial doesn't go well,

945
01:00:13,318 --> 01:00:17,155
everyone who was involved in the case
will get destroyed like dominos.

946
01:00:17,822 --> 01:00:19,616
We'll all go down. All of us.

947
01:00:19,699 --> 01:00:20,867
Right.

948
01:00:21,826 --> 01:00:23,077
I know.

949
01:00:30,793 --> 01:00:32,295
What a headache.

950
01:00:33,087 --> 01:00:36,215
But of course,
I'm sure it's worse for you.

951
01:00:36,883 --> 01:00:38,801
Why don't we go for a drink?

952
01:00:38,885 --> 01:00:41,512
No, I'm not in the mood for a drink.

953
01:00:42,597 --> 01:00:45,016
Have you visited Lee Dae-cheol recently?

954
01:00:46,267 --> 01:00:48,519
-Why would I go there?
-You're close with Lee Eun-hye.

955
01:00:49,812 --> 01:00:51,314
Has she ever asked you

956
01:00:51,397 --> 01:00:53,650
to save her dad saying he's innocent?

957
01:00:56,986 --> 01:00:59,989
You punk. Why are you asking me that?

958
01:01:02,200 --> 01:01:03,534
Why are you so agitated?

959
01:01:04,744 --> 01:01:07,205
What's going on?
Did she really ask you for help?

960
01:01:13,586 --> 01:01:17,590
Captain Nam, I joined the force
earlier than you.

961
01:01:18,841 --> 01:01:21,427
But you're a lot more successful
than I am.

962
01:01:24,806 --> 01:01:26,974
Don't be bothered by a guy like me.

963
01:01:27,767 --> 01:01:30,353
Once the retrial begins,
you'll get pulled into a mess

964
01:01:31,437 --> 01:01:33,731
regardless of the result.

965
01:01:33,815 --> 01:01:35,525
Just have pity on the kid

966
01:01:36,442 --> 01:01:39,153
and stay quiet.

967
01:01:39,987 --> 01:01:41,489
You're good at that.

968
01:01:42,281 --> 01:01:43,741
And one more thing.

969
01:01:44,784 --> 01:01:46,994
If you mess with a guy like me
who has nothing to lose…

970
01:01:49,163 --> 01:01:50,415
You should watch how you behave.

971
01:01:51,582 --> 01:01:52,917
You have no idea what I might do.

972
01:02:05,805 --> 01:02:07,306
Gosh, how scary.

973
01:02:13,646 --> 01:02:16,357
Why are you guys still at the office?

974
01:02:18,151 --> 01:02:20,862
Do-chang, what did Chief Moon say?

975
01:02:20,945 --> 01:02:23,698
Does he know you're behind all this?

976
01:02:23,781 --> 01:02:26,117
Pretend you know nothing.
Don't show that you know anything.

977
01:02:26,200 --> 01:02:27,994
If I ever need your help,

978
01:02:28,870 --> 01:02:30,246
I'll let you know.

979
01:02:30,329 --> 01:02:32,999
So if the chief asks,
tell him you don't know anything.

980
01:02:33,916 --> 01:02:35,877
You guys should go home. I'll leave later.

981
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:38,421
You should also go home.
I need to do something on my own.

982
01:02:39,505 --> 01:02:40,506
Okay.

983
01:02:48,556 --> 01:02:53,060
Lee Dae-cheol's retrial was possible
thanks to Do-chang and Ji-hyeok, right?

984
01:02:53,686 --> 01:02:54,896
Yes.

985
01:02:54,979 --> 01:02:57,815
I'm so impressed by Do-chang.

986
01:02:57,899 --> 01:02:59,567
What's there to be impressed about?

987
01:02:59,650 --> 01:03:03,404
What good will it do for him
if Lee Dae-cheol wins the trial?

988
01:03:03,488 --> 01:03:05,198
He'll just get hated by his superiors.

989
01:03:05,281 --> 01:03:07,617
Do-chang feels embarrassed. That's why.

990
01:03:07,700 --> 01:03:09,994
If he doesn't do anything,
he'll feel embarrassed forever.

991
01:03:10,077 --> 01:03:13,164
That's why he's doing this.
I know how he feels.

992
01:03:13,706 --> 01:03:16,876
I was very close
to humiliating myself as well,

993
01:03:16,959 --> 01:03:18,669
but Do-chang helped me come to my senses.

994
01:03:18,753 --> 01:03:21,214
And for the first time in my life,

995
01:03:21,297 --> 01:03:23,633
I realized why I need to be a detective.

996
01:03:23,716 --> 01:03:27,929
Don't you think this is Do-chang's way
of sending us a message?

997
01:03:28,012 --> 01:03:29,472
"This is what it means to be a cop.

998
01:03:29,555 --> 01:03:32,600
This is how you should live."

999
01:03:34,435 --> 01:03:36,562
I think I said something
really cool just now.

1000
01:03:37,647 --> 01:03:38,981
Don't you agree?

1001
01:03:39,065 --> 01:03:40,149
-Yes.
-Yes.

1002
01:03:40,900 --> 01:03:41,901
I'm impressed.

1003
01:03:43,027 --> 01:03:45,112
You little… Come here.

1004
01:04:00,628 --> 01:04:04,382
MURDER OF YOON JI-SEON AND JANG JIN-SU
LEE DAE-CHEOL'S INTERROGATION REPORT

1005
01:04:07,927 --> 01:04:09,178
KANG DO-CHANG

1006
01:04:25,528 --> 01:04:26,529
Sir.

1007
01:04:28,531 --> 01:04:29,657
Detective Kang.

1008
01:04:50,845 --> 01:04:53,097
Just kill me.

1009
01:04:53,180 --> 01:04:55,850
Why did you get my daughter involved? Why?

1010
01:04:55,933 --> 01:04:57,476
Tell me what you did wrong in detail.

1011
01:04:58,394 --> 01:05:00,062
I'll tell you at the police station.

1012
01:05:00,146 --> 01:05:02,607
Why would we go there?
This is a crime scene.

1013
01:05:02,690 --> 01:05:05,151
Did you find anything else
to prove that Oh Jong-tae is the culprit?

1014
01:05:05,234 --> 01:05:07,904
-Did Mr. Yoo ask you to find out?
-He's not that kind of a guy.

1015
01:05:07,987 --> 01:05:11,157
Have they found any evidence
that would make them suspect you?

1016
01:05:11,240 --> 01:05:12,742
You must've been in a hurry.

1017
01:05:12,825 --> 01:05:14,577
I admit that I crossed the centerline!

1018
01:05:15,077 --> 01:05:17,204
But I won't ever be going to court.

1019
01:05:17,288 --> 01:05:19,874
So what he's a detective?
Is it that important?

1020
01:05:21,208 --> 01:05:23,169
Your brother is a detective, okay?

1021
01:05:23,252 --> 01:05:24,879
Look at yourself.

1022
01:05:24,962 --> 01:05:27,673
Who do you think is
living in a mess right now?

1023
01:05:27,757 --> 01:05:29,508
Eun-hye asked me for help.

1024
01:05:29,592 --> 01:05:31,344
You must stay alive, Lee Dae-cheol.

1025
01:05:32,511 --> 01:05:37,516
